com.hazelcast.map.impl.query

Interface Result<T extends Result>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the result for the concrete implementations
    All Superinterfaces:
    DataSerializable, IdentifiedDataSerializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AggregationResult, QueryResult

    public interface Result<T extends Result>
extends IdentifiedDataSerializable
    Result of a Query. Each query type implements its own Result.

      • onCombineFinished

        void onCombineFinished()
        Invoked when the result combining phase is finished.

        Implementations may release intermediary resources associated with the combining. No further calls to combine(T) are expected after this method invocation.

        See Also:
        combine(Result)

      • add

        void add(QueryableEntry entry)
        Adds the given entry to this result.
        Parameters:
        entry - the entry to add.

      • createSubResult

        T createSubResult()
        Creates a new empty sub result of the same type as this result.

        This method is used by the query execution engine while constructing the partial sub results. These sub results are combined with this result during the final stage of the result construction.

        Returns:
        the created sub result.

      • orderAndLimit

        void orderAndLimit(PagingPredicate pagingPredicate,
                   Map.Entry<Integer,Map.Entry> nearestAnchorEntry)
        Performs the order-and-limit operation on this result for the given paging predicate.
        Parameters:
        pagingPredicate - the paging predicate to perform the operation for.
        nearestAnchorEntry - the anchor entry of the paging predicate.

      • completeConstruction

        void completeConstruction(Collection<Integer> partitionIds)
        Completes the construction of this result.

        Implementations may release intermediary resources associated with the construction in this method. No further modifications of the result are expected after this method invocation except combining the result with other results.

        Parameters:
        partitionIds - the partition IDs to associate this result with.
        See Also:
        combine(Result)
